GSM650498.characteristics_ch1: cell type: ovarian cancer cell;	cell line: OV90;	resistance type: doxorubicin resistant sub-line of OV90 was generated by exposure to the chemotherapeutic drug (Sigma) for four cycles.  For each cycle, the cells were exposed to the drug for twenty-four hours, and then transferred to normal media where they were allowed to grow for 2 weeks. Following this two-week period, the cells were re-exposed to the drug to initiate the next cycle for a total of 4 cycles.  Subclones were isolated and expanded after the last cycle.
